frameDefinitions: A Figure is (stably) located with respect to a Ground in terms of how the distance between them compares to some general or contextually relevant scale.
This frame is about the static comparison of an Profiled_item to a Standard_item, often  with respect to some Attribute.
One Part of a larger Whole has been mentioned, is inferrable, or is available in the discourse setting and the previously unmentioned part, the Rest, is now mentioned.
An Item is located on a Scale relative to a critical value which is determined by some Enabled_situation.
A mutual social and personal relationship that keeps people involved in each other's lives comprises a Connection of Individual1 to Individual
frameExamples: The Sun is putting on a show that <t>rivals</t> the most sizzling Hollywood thrillers.
The lenses , like the <t><fex name='Rest'>rest</fex></t> of the exoskeleton, are made of calcite.
They wanted to strengthen their family <t>ties</t>.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Ground</fen> serves as a basis for describing the location of the <fen>Figure</fen>.
The <fen>Figure</fen> is perceived as located relative to a certain <fen>Ground</fen> location. The figure can be an entity or an event.
The period of time during which the locative relation between <fen>Figure</fen> and <fen>Ground</fen> obtains.
In active sentences, the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> is the grammatically more prominent one of the items that are compared and realized as  the subject. .
In active setnnces, the <fen>Standard_item</fen> is  the grammatically less prominent element, i.e. the object or an oblique.
This Frame Elements marks constituents that indicate in which respect Item-1 and Item-2 are equal to each other.
The <fen>Standard_attribute</fen> is used when the standard is a specific value on  a scale.
The <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen> is a particular value on a scale which is being compared to a <fen>Standard_item</fen> or <fen>Profiled_attribute</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Profiled_item</fen> rivals the <fen>Standard_item</fen>.
A <fen>Part</fen> of a larger <fen>Whole</fen> that has been mentioned in prior discourse or is available in the discourse setting.
The previously unmentioned part of the <fen>Whole</fen>.
The larger entitiy or group that is fully made up of the <fen>Part</fen> and the <fen>Rest</fen>.
The entity whose scalar property is specified.
The <fen>Scale</fen> is the attribute of the <fen>Item</fen> that is being described.
This role identifies the <fen>Enabled_situation</fen> by which the critical value is judged.
<fen>Individuals</fen> have a <fen>Connection</fen> with each other.
<fen>Individual1</fen> has a social <fen>Connection</fen> to <fen>Individual_2</fen>.
<fen>Individual2</fen> has a relationship to <fen>Individual_1</fen>.
<fen>Connection</fen> is the personal relationship between <fen>Individuals</fen> that keeps them involved in each other's lives.
